olive oil
1 packet freekeh
15 g butter
1 portion cauliflower
1 carrot
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 sachet ras el hanout
1 packet beef strips
½ lemon
1 tsp honey
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag herbs
2 clove garlic
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic. Rinse the freekeh.
• In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Toast freekeh, stirring
occasionally, until golden, 1-2 minutes.
• Half-fill the saucepan with water, then add
a good pinch of salt. Bring to the boil, then
simmer, uncovered, until tender, 30-35 minutes.
Drain and rinse freekeh, then set aside.
• Return pan to medium heat, then add the butter
and garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Return freekeh to the pan and stir to combine.

TIP: The freekeh is cooked when it has softened but
still retains some bite.

• Meanwhile, cut cauliflower into small florets.
Cut carrot into bite-sized chunks.
• Place the veggies on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle
over chermoula spice blend, drizzle with olive
oil and season with salt. Toss to coat, spread out
evenly, then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• While the veggies are roasting, combine ras el
hanout, a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt
and pepper in a medium bowl. Add beef strips,
toss to coat and set aside.

• Zest lemon to get a pinch, then slice
into wedges.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt
and a squeeze of lemon juice. Set aside.

• When freekeh has 5 minutes cook time
remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook beef strips in
batches, until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, return all beef to the
pan, then add the honey and toss beef to coat.
Set aside.
• To the saucepan with cooked freekeh, add
roasted veggies, baby spinach leaves, lemon
zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and torn herbs.
Stir to combine and season to taste.

• Divide roast veggie freekeh between plates.
Top with Moroccan honey beef.
• Dollop over lemon yoghurt. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!